The paper deals with the construction of spanners, which is a well-studied topic in the area of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the approximation of distances, which is a common theme in numerical algorithms (cs.NA) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for constructing pairwise spanners, which could be considered a topic in social networks (cs.SI) or graph theory (cs.DM).
